# Repo-root .gitignore.
#
# The project sources live under rag/. There's a more detailed
# rag/.gitignore that handles the Python build artifacts, IDE noise,
# and corpus-level exclusions. This top-level file exists because
# the virtualenv was created at the repo root (not inside rag/), and
# patterns in rag/.gitignore only match files reachable from rag/.
#
# Add patterns here when they need to apply above/rag/ (such as the
# virtualenv that lives one level up from the sources).

# --- Virtualenv created in this directory ---
.venv/

# --- Local tooling state ---
.codegraph/

# --- Stray launcher artifacts from PowerShell mishaps ---
.venvScriptspython.exe
*PYTHONPATH
